    "body": "The accelerated lookup using CPython internals is never used because CPython always has vectorcall these days, so remove it. (Marginally, it could be used if the user has manually disabled vectorcall, but it doesn't seem worth keeping optimizations around for that possibility.)\r\n\r\nAlso simplify the condition attached to it. It's essentially `!CYTHON_VECTORCALL || (__PYX_LIMITED_VERSION_HEX < 3.12 && CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API)`. The limited API part is implicit in the definition of `CYTHON_VECTORCALL` anyway.",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-12T17:49:58Z",
