                },
                "message": "Simplify __Pyx_PyObject_GetMethod\n\nThe accelerated lookup using CPython internals is never used\nbecause CPython always has vectorcall these days, so remove it.\n(Marginally, it could be used if the user has manually disabled\nvectorcall, but it doesn't seem worth keeping optimizations\naround for that possibility.)\n\nAlso simplify the condition attached to it. It's essentially\n`!CYTHON_VECTORCALL || (__PYX_LIMITED_VERSION_HEX < 3.12 && CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API)`.\nThe limited API part is implicit in the definition of `CYTHON_VECTORCALL`\nanyway.",
